name: analyticsadmin_properties_createSubproperty
description: Create a subproperty and a subproperty event filter that applies to the created subproperty.

fields.description: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

key.description: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

oauth_token.description: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

prettyPrint.description: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

quotaUser.description: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters.

parent.description: Required. The ordinary property for which to create a subproperty. Format: properties/property_id Example: properties/123

GoogleAnalyticsAdminV1alphaProperty.description: A resource message representing a Google Analytics GA4 property.

account.description: Immutable. The resource name of the parent account Format: accounts/{account_id} Example: "accounts/123"

createTime.description: Output only. Time when the entity was originally created.

currencyCode.description: The currency type used in reports involving monetary values. Format: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217 Examples: "USD", "EUR", "JPY"

deleteTime.description: Output only. If set, the time at which this property was trashed. If not set, then this property is not currently in the trash can.

displayName.description: Required. Human-readable display name for this property. The max allowed display name length is 100 UTF-16 code units.

expireTime.description: Output only. If set, the time at which this trashed property will be permanently deleted. If not set, then this property is not currently in the trash can and is not slated to be deleted.

industryCategory.description: Industry associated with this property Example: AUTOMOTIVE, FOOD_AND_DRINK

name.description: Output only. Resource name of this property. Format: properties/{property_id} Example: "properties/1000"

parent.description: Immutable. Resource name of this property's logical parent. Note: The Property-Moving UI can be used to change the parent. Format: accounts/{account}, properties/{property} Example: "accounts/100", "properties/101"

propertyType.description: Immutable. The property type for this Property resource. When creating a property, if the type is "PROPERTY_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED", then "ORDINARY_PROPERTY" will be implied.

serviceLevel.description: Output only. The Google Analytics service level that applies to this property.

timeZone.description: Required. Reporting Time Zone, used as the day boundary for reports, regardless of where the data originates. If the time zone honors DST, Analytics will automatically adjust for the changes. NOTE: Changing the time zone only affects data going forward, and is not applied retroactively. Format: https://www.iana.org/time-zones Example: "America/Los_Angeles"

updateTime.description: Output only. Time when entity payload fields were last updated.

GoogleAnalyticsAdminV1alphaSubpropertyEv.description: A resource message representing a GA4 Subproperty event filter.

applyToProperty.description: Immutable. Resource name of the Subproperty that uses this filter.

filterClauses.description: Required. Unordered list. Filter clauses that define the SubpropertyEventFilter. All clauses are AND'ed together to determine what data is sent to the subproperty.

GoogleAnalyticsAdminV1alphaSubpropertyEv.description: A clause for defining a filter. A filter may be inclusive (events satisfying the filter clause are included in the subproperty's data) or exclusive (events satisfying the filter clause are excluded from the subproperty's data).

filterClauseType.description: Required. The type for the filter clause.

GoogleAnalyticsAdminV1alphaSubpropertyEv.description: A logical expression of Subproperty event filters.

fieldName.description: Required. The field that is being filtered.

GoogleAnalyticsAdminV1alphaSubpropertyEv.description: A filter for a string-type dimension that matches a particular pattern.

caseSensitive.description: Optional. If true, the string value is case sensitive. If false, the match is case-insensitive.

matchType.description: Required. The match type for the string filter.

value.description: Required. The string value used for the matching.

GoogleAnalyticsAdminV1alphaSubpropertyEv.description: A list of Subproperty event filter expressions.

filterExpressions.description: Required. Unordered list. A list of Subproperty event filter expressions
